      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "DUTY (1) resumed this course and distance and was simply too strong, scoring by a length after racing on speed. Great record course and distance and has a low draw. Can only be fitter and worth following up. BODMIN BOY (2) was also a winner last time but over 1400m. Yet to win this trip but same field suits and should keep coming. STARTON (4) was narrowly beaten behind BODMIN BOY and meets him much better at the weights. Also unproven over the mile but gets chance to turn the tables. MATRON SAMSING (3) placed last time and meets winner better at the weights. Worth keeping safe. MUMMSIE (5) can give a sight off the low draw.",
